                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the President of the Pan American Airways, Inc.</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">J. T. Trippe</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-01">April 1,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram, April 1. The Department greatly appreciates the fine cooperation
                    which the Pan American Airways is giving in connection with the disaster at
                    Managua. Your message has been brought to the attention of the Red Cross and the
                    Navy Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William J. Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
